          "text": "No — not in any meaningful way. A standard serving of beef organ supplements (6 capsules, roughly 3,000mg) contains approximately 2–3 grams of protein at most. These are micronutrient supplements, not protein sources. They support the hormonal and cellular environment that makes muscle protein synthesis work — but they don't replace hitting your daily protein target of 120–160g."
        }
      },
